### Output form errors

You can output the name of the field related to the error, and the error message, by using the error as a key to access the `translated_fields` and `messages` properties.

```liquid
<ul>
  {% for error in form.errors %}
    <li>
      {% if error == 'form' %}
        {{ form.errors.messages[error] }}
      {% else %}
        {{ form.errors.translated_fields[error] }} - {{ form.errors.messages[error] }}
      {% endif %}
    </li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
```

Because of this, you should use \<code>\<span class="PreventFireFoxApplyingGapToWBR">line\<wbr/>\_item.product.has\<wbr/>\_only\<wbr/>\_default\<wbr/>\_variant\</span>\</code> to check whether there\&#39;s any information to output.

