These names are also built-in Liquid filters that can be applied using dot notation, and square bracket notation always looks up the metafield by key. With dot notation, such as \<code>resource.metafields.namespace.size\</code>, Liquid returns the metafield if it exists, but applies the filter to the namespace if the metafield is missing. For example, \<code>size\</code> returns the metafield count instead of an empty value.

